@Weissnix4711 thanks for the additional info. Yes, this is the difference between `Wants` and `Requires`.

If service A `Wants` service B, systemd will attempt to start service B, but will start service A regardless to service B's status. Also, stopping service B will not affect service A.
If service A `Requires` service B, systemd will attempt to start service B and (assuming `After` was also set) will not start service A if service B failed to start. Also, stopping service B will trigger systemd to stop service A.

